article.headline: Kansas St. 67, No. 25 Colorado 60
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Kimberly Dietz scored 18 points and Kansas State rallied to beat No. 25 Colorado 67-60 Saturday night.

Kansas State extended its winning streak to seven and improved to 4-0 in the Big 12 for the first time since 2004. The Wildcats, who just missed entering the latest rankings, should have a good shot at moving into the Top 25 with the victory over Colorado (12-5, 1-3).

Dietz powered a 21-4 second-half run for Kansas State, nailing two 3-pointers and assisting on four other baskets as the Wildcats turned a three-point deficit into a 62-49 advantage with 4:04 remaining.

Shalee Lehning had 11 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists for Kansas State (12-5, 4-0), which has won 11 straight home games by an average of nearly 30 points. Marlies Gipson added 14 points and Ashley Sweat 12.

Kansas native Jackie McFarland had 20 points and 11 rebounds to lead the Buffaloes, who have been in the Top 25 for four straight weeks but likely will fall out of the rankings after losing three straight.

Colorado struggled to get anything going offensively for much of the second half, and at one point turned the ball over on five consecutive possessions. Freshman Brittany Spears scored 16 points and Aija Putnina added 12 for the Buffaloes, who shot 4-of-16 from 3-point range and committed 17 turnovers.

Dietz hit a 3-pointer from the top of the key just before halftime to give the Wildcats a 35-31 lead at the break.
